      "writtenOn": "2026-02-06T21:37:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since the schema file is being dropped, you should delete lines 84-90 here.\n\nIf I\u0027m understanding things correctly, the file format currently consists of two JSON object types: ChassisPowerMonitor and GPIO.\n\nYou might consider simplifying the first JSON object type name to just Chassis, since each one represents properties of a chassis.\n\nThe outermost part of the file format is an array of Chassis objects.\n```\n[\n  Chassis,\n  Chassis,\n  Chassis\n]\n```\n\nEach Chassis object has the properties you describe below. Most of them have a value of a GPIO object. That object type has properties too.\n\nYou can document both object types here + the overall config file format, but that might get a bit confusing. I would recommend creating chassis.md and gpio.md files that each cover one object type. You can give a description of the object, show the properties, and have an example at the bottom if you wish.\n\nThen in the README you could state the overall format is an array of Chassis objects and put in a link to the chassis.md file for more information. The chassis.md would have a link to the gpio.md file next to the gpio properties.\n\nSee the phosphor-regulators or phosphor-power-sequencer docs/config_file directories for examples you can copy/paste.",
      "revId": "db4957c145995d187c52c517ee3ee64c8bbd380f",
